00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:37,080
开发一系列的元素
for what they call a graphical user interface.

195
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:38,240
也许你听说过
Maybe you've heard of it.

196
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:43,680
它们有菜单、滚动条、按钮、文件夹和层叠的窗口
They've got menus, they've got scroll bars, they've got buttons and folders and overlapping windows.

197
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:49,840
这是对计算机界面的一个前所未有的美丽新设想
It was a beautiful new vision of what a computer interface could look like. And nobody had any of this stuff.

198
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:53,280
作家兼记者 Steve Levy 谈到了它的潜力
Author and journalist Steven Levy talks about its potential.

199
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:58,040
有很多人为这个新界面令人感到激动
There was a lot of excitement about this new interface

200
00:11:58,040 --> 00:12:02,280
它比以前的交互界面更友好
that was going to be much friendlier than what we had before,

201
00:12:02,280 --> 00:12:04,400
以前用的交互界面被称为命令行 
which used what was called the command line,

202
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:13,040
这不是在现实生活中使用的交互方式
where there was really no interaction between you and the computer in the way you'd interact with something in real life.

203
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:18,600
鼠标和电脑上的图像
The mouse and the graphics on the computer gave you a way to do that,

204
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:21,560
让你可以像指向现实生活中的东西一样 指向电脑上的东西
to point to something just like you'd point to something in real life.

205
00:12:21,560 --> 00:12:24,760
这让事情变得简单多了 你不需要记住那些代码
It made it a lot easier. You didn't have to memorize all these codes.

206
00:12:24,760 --> 00:12:30,200
