Except, the Xerox executives did not get that they were sitting on top of a platinum mine.

207
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:33,720
一如既往地 工程师比主管们更清楚它的价值
The engineers were more aware than the execs. Typical.

208
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:35,720
因此那些工程师
So those engineers were, yeah,

209
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:40,040
在被要求向乔布斯展示这些东西是如何工作时 有点紧张
a little stressed out that they were instructed to show Jobs how everything worked.

210
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:42,200
然而这毕竟是高管的命令
But the executives were calling the shots.

211
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:43,560
用乔布斯的话来说 他认为
Jobs felt, quote,

