You're probably familiar with his work.

306
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:37,280
他想要拥有自由软件的自由社会
He wanted free software and a free society.

307
00:18:37,280 --> 00:18:38,840
这就像言论自由一样的自由
That's free as in free speech,

308
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:40,080
而不是像免费啤酒一样的免费
not free as in free beer.

309
00:18:40,080 --> 00:18:42,440
早在 80 年代 斯托尔曼就发现
Back in the '80s, Stallman saw that

310
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:44,240
除了昂贵的专有操作系统（如 UNIX）外
there was no viable alternative

311
00:18:44,240 --> 00:18:47,440
没有其他可行的替代品
to pricey, proprietary OSs, like UNIX .

312
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:49,720
因此他决定自己做一个
So, he decided to make his own.

313
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:52,520
斯托尔曼的自由软件基金会开发了 GNU
Stallman's Free Software Foundation developed GNU,

314
00:18:52,520 --> 00:18:54,640
当然 它的意思是 “GNU's not UNIX”
which stood for GNU's not UNIX , of course.

315
00:18:54,640 --> 00:18:56,760
它将是一个像 UNIX 一样的操作系统
It'd be an OS like UNIX,

316
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:58,400
但不包含 UNIX 代码
but free of all UNIX code,

317
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:00,400
而且所有用户可以自由共享它
and free for users to share.

318
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:05,400
为了让你体会到上世纪 80 年代自由软件概念的重要性
Just to give you a sense of how important that idea of free software was in the 1980s,

319
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:08,400
从不同角度来说拥有 UNIX 代码的两家公司
the companies that owned the UNIX code at different points,

