And that would have made almost anyone who had worked on a computer operating system that involved UNIX ,

334
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:08,480
以及任何在计算机科学部门工作的人
and any computer science department that was in the country,

335
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:10,080
都受到了精神上的污染
was mentally contaminated.

336
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:11,760
在 USENIX 的一年里
So in one year at USENIX,

337
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:15,160
我们都得到了一个写着红色字母的白色小别针
we all got little white bar pins with red letters

338
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:16,800
上面写着“精神受到了污染”
that say mentally contaminated,

339
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:21,640
我们很喜欢带着这些别针到处走
and we all wear those around to our own great pleasure,

340
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:25,240
表达我们在这件事上对贝尔实验室的讽刺
to show that we were sticking it to Bell because we were mentally contaminated.

341
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:28,320
整个世界都被精神污染了
The whole world was getting mentally contaminated.

342
00:20:28,320 --> 00:20:31,360
想要保持纯粹、保持事物的美好
Staying pure, keeping things nice and proprietary,

343
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:34,840
和完整地拥有一个软件的旧思想正变得越来越不现实
that old philosophy was getting less and less realistic.

344
00:20:34,840 --> 00:20:37,480
正是在这被污染的现实中
It was into this contaminated reality

345
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:41,160
历史上最伟大的代码英雄之一诞生了
that one of history's biggest command line heroes was born,

346
00:20:41,160 --> 00:20:44,400
他是一个芬兰男孩 名叫林纳斯·托瓦兹
a boy in Finland named Linus Torvalds.

347
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:48,200
如果这是《星球大战》 那么林纳斯·托瓦兹就是我们的卢克·天行者
If this is Star Wars, then Linus Torvalds is our Luke Skywalker.

348
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:51,440
他是赫尔辛基大学的一名温文尔雅的研究生
He was a mild-mannered grad student at the University of Helsinki.

349
00:20:51,440 --> 00:20:54,160
有才华 但缺乏大志
Talented, but lacking in grand visions.

350
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:56,080
典型的被逼上梁山的英雄
The classic reluctant hero.

351
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:59,480
和其他年轻的英雄一样 他也感到沮丧
And, like any young hero, he was also frustrated.

352
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:05,360
他想把 386 处理器整合到他的新电脑中
He wanted to incorporate the 386 processor into his new PC's functions.

353
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:08,760
他对自己兼容 IBM 的电脑上运行 MS-DOS 操作系统并不感冒
He wasn't impressed by the MS-DOS running on his IBM clone,

354
00:21:08,760 --> 00:21:13,280
也负担不起 UNIX 软件 5000 美元的价格
and he couldn't afford the $5,000 price tag on the UNIX software

355
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:16,080
但只有 UNIX 才能让他自由地编程
that would have given him some programming freedom.

356
00:21:16,080 --> 00:21:20,280
解决方案是 托瓦兹在 1991 年春天
The solution, which Torvalds crafted on MINIX in the spring of 1991,

357
00:21:20,280 --> 00:21:23,160
基于 MINIX 开发了一个名为 Linux 的操作系统内核
was an OS kernel called Linux.

358
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:25,640
他自己的操作系统内核
The kernel of an OS of his very own.

359
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:31,720
林纳斯·托瓦兹真的只是想找点乐子而已
Linus Torvalds really just wanted to have something to play with.

360
00:21:31,720 --> 00:21:35,600
Steven Vaughan-Nichols 是 ZDNet.com 的特约编辑
Steven Vaughan-Nichols is a contributing editor at ZDNet.com,

361
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:40,160
