and he's been writing about the business of technology since there was a business of technology.

362
00:21:40,160 --> 00:21:44,280
当时有几个类似的操作系统
There were a couple of operating systems like it at the time.

363
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:48,240
他最关注的是一个名叫 MINIX 
The main one that he was concerned about was called MINIX,

364
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:55,320
旨在让学生学习如何构建操作系统的项目
and that was an operating system that was meant for students to learn how to build operating systems.

365
00:21:55,320 --> 00:21:58,960
林纳斯看到了这些并且觉得它很有趣
Linus looked at that, and thought that it was interesting,

366
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:00,560
但他打算建立自己的操作系统
but he wanted to build his own.

367
00:22:00,560 --> 00:22:06,120
所以 Linux 实际上始于赫尔辛基的一个 DIY 项目
So it really started as a do-it-yourself project at Helsinki.

368
00:22:06,120 --> 00:22:08,840
一切就这样开始了
And that's how it all started,

369
00:22:08,840 --> 00:22:16,000
基本上就是一个大孩子在玩耍 学习如何做些什么
it's just basically a big kid playing around and learning how to do things.

370
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:25,920
但不同之处在于 他足够聪明、足够执着
But what was different in his case is that he was both bright enough and persistent enough,

371
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:31,200
也足够友好 能让其他人都参与进来
and also friendly enough to get all these other people working on it,

372
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:33,680
然后他开始把这个项目进行到底
and then he started seeing the project through.

373
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:39,400
27 年后 这个项目变得比他想象的要大得多
27 years later, it is much, much bigger than he ever dreamed it would be.

374
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:45,760
到 1991 年秋季 托瓦兹发布了 10000 行代码
By the fall of 1991, Torvalds releases 10,000 lines of code,

375
00:22:45,760 --> 00:22:48,560
世界各地的人们开始评头论足
and people around the world start offering comments,

376
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:51,000
然后进行优化、添加和修改代码
then tweaks, additions, edits.

377
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:53,800
对于今天的开发人员来说似乎很正常
That might seem totally normal to you as a developer today,

378
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:55,720
但请记住 在那个时候
but remember, at that time,

379
00:22:55,720 --> 00:23:00,560
开放协作操作系统是对微软、苹果和 IBM
open collaboration like that was a moral affront to the whole proprietary system

380
00:23:00,560 --> 00:23:04,000
这些靠专利盈利的公司的精神侮辱
that Microsoft, Apple, and IBM had done so well by.

381
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:06,920
随后这种开放性被奉上神坛
And then that openness gets enshrined.

382
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:10,920
托瓦兹将 Linux 置于 GNU 通用公共许可证之下
Torvalds places Linux under the GNU general public license.

383
00:23:10,920 --> 00:23:13,920
曾经保障斯托尔曼的 GNU 系统自由的许可证
The license that had kept Stallman's GNU system free

384
00:23:13,920 --> 00:23:15,840
现在也将保障 Linux 的自由
was now going to keep Linux free, too.

385
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:18,800
GPL 许可基本上能永远保证软件的自由和开放性
The importance of that move to incorporate GPL,

386
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:23,880
它的重要性被怎么强调都不过分
basically preserving the freedom and openness of the software forever, cannot be overstated.

387
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:25,880
Vaughan-Nichols 解释道
Vaughan-Nichols explains.

388
00:23:25,880 --> 00:23:28,040
事实上 根据 Linux 所遵循的许可协议
In fact, by the license that it's under,

389
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:30,600
即 GPL 第 2 版
which is called GPL version 2,

390
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:32,480
如果你想贩卖 Linux 或者向全世界展示它
you have to share the code

391
00:23:32,480 --> 00:23:37,320
你必须与他人共享代码
if you're going to try to sell it or present it to the world,

392
00:23:37,320 --> 00:23:40,040
所以如果你对其做了一些改进
so that if you make an improvement,

